                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4478/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-10-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 5, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Wilson states that the situation in the Province of Corrientes is serious,
                    but confined to that Province, and that several fights have taken place between
                    the revolutionary and government forces. Informs Mr. Root that <hi rend="italic"
                        >Las Palmas</hi>, a steamer belonging to an American citizen, has been
                    seized by the revolutionists and that he has requested the Government to take
                    the necessary measures for its return. Says that the revolutionists have taken
                    two boats belonging to Italian subjects.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
